WEBVTT

00:05.480 --> 00:06.480
Neigh.

00:10.920 --> 00:13.840
-Was that it?
-Yeah, that's all it says here.

00:17.200 --> 00:20.880
Steven, we think the "neigh" is probably
meant to be the sound of a horse.

00:20.960 --> 00:22.760
You want me to make the sound of a horse?

00:22.840 --> 00:25.400
Yeah, I'm guessing the "neigh"
is just a rough indication.

00:25.480 --> 00:27.800
-So just do the sound of a horse.
-All right.

00:30.080 --> 00:32.240
[neighs]

00:36.080 --> 00:38.040
-Hi, Steven, this is Clem Fandango.
-Mm.

00:38.120 --> 00:39.120
-Can you hear me?
-Yes.

00:39.200 --> 00:41.560
The feeling here is
that didn't sound much like a horse.

00:41.640 --> 00:43.480
-What?
-Would it help that instead of a neigh

00:43.560 --> 00:44.880
-you can try a whinny?
-A what?

00:44.960 --> 00:46.880
A whinny might be better than a neigh.

00:46.960 --> 00:48.240
What's the difference?

00:48.320 --> 00:51.000
-Just do another horse sound.
-Think whinny rather than neigh.

00:54.040 --> 00:56.880
Whin-neigh!

01:01.880 --> 01:04.800
Steven, was that a whinny?
'Cause that sounded a lot like a neigh.

01:04.879 --> 01:07.160
Jesus Christ, look, I've got things to do.

01:07.240 --> 01:11.040
And one of those is not sitting with you
two pilchards making horse noises.

01:13.000 --> 01:15.360
-What are you doing?
-Just googling whinny and neigh.

01:15.440 --> 01:17.240
Oh, for fuck's...

01:17.320 --> 01:21.000
Why don't you just bring a horse in here?
Yeah? I'm sure he'd nail it first time.

01:21.080 --> 01:22.840
Health and safety issue, Steven.

01:22.920 --> 01:27.200
Sorry, Steven, I got this so wrong.
It's actually  Neigh-bours.

01:28.280 --> 01:30.120
-Neighbours?
-Yeah, it's my fault.

01:30.200 --> 01:32.680
The whole script didn't print out.
I just got a bit of it.

01:32.760 --> 01:34.000
[Toast] You're an idiot.

01:36.680 --> 01:37.720
[Toast] Are we rolling?

01:38.760 --> 01:42.400
"Neighbours,  returning to Channel 5
this autumn.

01:42.480 --> 01:47.240
Don't miss it. Every weekday at 5:30pm."

02:22.600 --> 02:24.360
Breakfast's ready, Toast!

02:30.400 --> 02:31.560
[screams]

02:32.600 --> 02:34.440
[groans]

02:37.640 --> 02:39.080
[screams]

02:41.400 --> 02:43.400
Are you sure you don't want me
to call an ambulance?

02:44.120 --> 02:46.400
You've just crashed
through a complete flight of stairs

02:46.480 --> 02:49.320
-and been hit by falling masonry.
-No, no, no, no.

02:49.400 --> 02:51.320
Just wearing the bandage should suffice.

02:51.400 --> 02:55.280
Anyway, I've gotta get a wriggle on,
otherwise I'll be late for maths.

02:55.360 --> 02:56.800
-Maths?
-No, um...

02:57.800 --> 03:00.280
Bill. I've gotta go and pay my bar bill.

03:00.360 --> 03:03.320
Maths. It's like you're off to school
and I'm your mum.

03:03.400 --> 03:06.600
What are you talking about?
Perhaps you should see a doctor.

03:07.600 --> 03:08.880
Good night.

03:12.960 --> 03:15.520
There you go, Ian.
Sorry it's all in coins.

03:15.600 --> 03:17.080
Look, I'll give you the rest later.

03:18.080 --> 03:20.240
Blair? What the hell are you doing here?

03:20.320 --> 03:21.360
You'd better sit down.

03:21.440 --> 03:22.920
-I am sitting down.
-No, you're not!

03:23.880 --> 03:25.560
No, I'm not. Please sit down.

03:27.720 --> 03:29.600
It's father. He's dying.

03:29.680 --> 03:31.360
That's a pity. Would you like a drink?

03:31.440 --> 03:33.240
-Why the hell are you wearing that?
-What?

03:33.320 --> 03:36.360
-There's a bandage on your head.
-I crashed through some stairs.

03:37.600 --> 03:38.720
I think.

03:38.800 --> 03:41.160
Well, as they say,
father's days are numbered.

03:41.240 --> 03:43.440
-Doctor reckons he'll be dead by Friday.
-So you said.

03:43.520 --> 03:45.000
So we need to get down there pronto

03:45.080 --> 03:47.720
and make sure he doesn't leave everything
to the bloody dog!

03:47.800 --> 03:49.080
Or worse still, the servants.

03:49.160 --> 03:52.600
Who cares?
He's never given a rat's arse about me.

03:52.680 --> 03:54.400
Tells everyone I'm dead.

03:54.480 --> 03:57.520
-I don't want anything from him.
-Yes, but I do, you bloody idiot!

03:57.600 --> 03:59.920
Think about it, Toast. Think!

04:00.000 --> 04:02.880
If I get the country castle,
you get the London pad.

04:03.640 --> 04:05.400
-The London pad?
-Hmm.

04:05.480 --> 04:09.560
Yeah, no rent, and wouldn't have to listen
to Ed's lovemaking marathons.

04:10.160 --> 04:13.120
Exactly, so we need to get down there
jaldi, jaldi , hmm?

04:13.640 --> 04:17.600
Right, I'm off to get the National Express
at Victoria Coach Station.

04:18.680 --> 04:22.200
The old family home could already
be crawling with oily freeloaders.

04:22.280 --> 04:25.760
We have to make sure we get to him first.
We can't leave anything to chance.

04:25.840 --> 04:28.120
-Are we clear?
-[mimics] Are we clear?

04:28.560 --> 04:31.080
Now you need to take this
very seriously, Toast.

04:31.160 --> 04:33.480
I don't wanna get down there
and find myself outnumbered.

04:33.560 --> 04:34.680
All right.

04:34.760 --> 04:36.560
Now, how do I get out
of this bugger house?

04:38.560 --> 04:43.400
[Jane] 50, 55, 60.

04:43.480 --> 04:44.640
What, more coins?

04:44.720 --> 04:47.440
Sorry, Toast, they only had change.

04:47.520 --> 04:49.000
But it's the BBC.

04:49.080 --> 04:51.600
Can't they make a direct payment
into my account or something?

04:51.680 --> 04:55.600
The people who make direct payments
have all moved to Salford.

04:55.680 --> 04:58.800
Sign of the times, I'm afraid.
Massive cutbacks.

04:59.400 --> 05:01.160
Why are you all glammed up, Jane?

05:02.080 --> 05:04.120
I'm meeting Jon Hamm.

05:05.520 --> 05:07.200
I've literally never heard of him.

05:07.280 --> 05:09.920
Probably one of the best actors
in the world.

05:10.000 --> 05:11.040
[scoffs]

05:11.120 --> 05:13.280
Surprised you've literally
never heard of him.

05:13.360 --> 05:16.960
He's fabulous, sexy
and terrifically good-looking.

05:17.560 --> 05:20.520
He's on a short break
from filming that Tommy Cooper film

05:20.600 --> 05:22.040
-in Dorset.
-[sighs]

05:22.120 --> 05:26.200
I'm meeting him upstairs at The Colonial.
Why don't you come along and say hello?

05:26.280 --> 05:27.480
No, I'm not interested.

05:27.560 --> 05:31.600
-He is hugely charismatic!
-[scoffs] Is he indeed?

05:32.680 --> 05:36.160
You know something? I've never met anyone
with any charisma, ever.

05:36.600 --> 05:38.440
It's a complete myth.

05:38.520 --> 05:40.800
Even that time I was introduced
to Sean Connery.

05:40.880 --> 05:43.000
It was like meeting a chair
or a dead rabbit.

05:43.080 --> 05:47.960
Well, everybody, people of every sex
and all sizes and shapes

05:48.040 --> 05:50.560
and ethnic groups, adore Hamm.

05:50.640 --> 05:53.080
Hmm. I'm not interested.

05:53.160 --> 05:55.400
But it just so happens,
I now have the exact money

05:55.480 --> 05:59.840
to pay my bar tab at The Colonial.
So I'll walk with you.

06:01.040 --> 06:02.920
[mumbles] Bloody ridiculous.

06:05.760 --> 06:07.880
That'll do you. Right, I'm off.

06:07.960 --> 06:10.520
Give my regards to West Ham
or whatever his name is.

06:10.600 --> 06:12.880
-Are you sure you won't stay for a drink?
-Jane.

06:12.960 --> 06:15.480
Like I told you,
I've absolutely no interest

06:15.560 --> 06:17.240
what...so...

06:17.560 --> 06:18.560
[singers]  ♪ Hamm! ♪

06:18.640 --> 06:20.240
[jazzy music]

06:21.240 --> 06:22.280
Jane!

06:22.360 --> 06:25.560
[Jane] Oh, how lovely to see you, Jonny.

06:25.640 --> 06:26.640
[singers]  ♪ Hamm! ♪

06:27.080 --> 06:29.120
Oh, this is Steven Toast.

06:29.680 --> 06:30.680
He's not staying.

06:30.760 --> 06:32.200
[mumbles]

06:34.080 --> 06:36.680
Well, it's... nice to meet you anyway.

06:38.200 --> 06:40.440
Where are you off to? Home to Ed?

06:41.160 --> 06:43.800
Who's Ed? Is that your husband?
Are you homosexual?

06:43.880 --> 06:45.800
-Ha!
-[nervous laughter]

06:45.880 --> 06:47.640
No, I was... [mumbles]

06:49.240 --> 06:51.400
[mumbles]

06:55.240 --> 06:58.160
-Do you know, I might stay.
-[singers]  ♪ Hamm! ♪

06:58.240 --> 07:01.040
I can't believe he's actually doing it.
Can you imagine?

07:01.320 --> 07:03.680
-What do you think, Toast?
-[jazzy music]

07:03.760 --> 07:06.000
-What?
-[Jane] Mark Rylance

07:06.080 --> 07:09.520
in the jungle celebrity
Get Me Out of Here!  show.

07:09.600 --> 07:10.880
What have you done to your head?

07:11.840 --> 07:13.920
Some stairs collapsed on top of me.

07:14.680 --> 07:18.160
Are you OK? You seem a bit... weird.

07:18.240 --> 07:20.440
[Jane] You're not yourself are you, Toast?

07:20.520 --> 07:24.040
Poor dear. Could you go and get us
some more drinks?

07:24.520 --> 07:26.960
What? Get some drinks?

07:27.040 --> 07:30.160
Yes. Some more of your drinks please, Ian.

07:30.240 --> 07:32.960
Excuse me. Are you Steven Toast?

07:33.400 --> 07:35.040
Maybe. So what if I am?

07:35.120 --> 07:37.280
My name is Pooky Hook.

07:37.360 --> 07:41.720
I have to say, I'm a huge fan of yours.
I'm an actress and model.

07:41.800 --> 07:44.960
I would love to meet up
for a drink or something,

07:45.040 --> 07:48.440
so you could give me some
acting and modeling tips.

07:49.320 --> 07:51.800
Look, this is my night off.

07:51.880 --> 07:54.280
If you wanna get in touch,
you'll have to go through my agent.

07:57.000 --> 07:59.760
I have to go to the Savile Row
and buy some shirts.

07:59.840 --> 08:03.520
Well, it's been delightful, Jonny.

08:03.600 --> 08:04.880
Can I come?

08:04.960 --> 08:05.960
-Hm?
-What?

08:06.040 --> 08:07.320
Can I come to the Savile Row?

08:08.160 --> 08:10.280
I thought you had something important
to attend to.

08:10.360 --> 08:13.080
No, well, that can wait. I'd rather go
to the Savile Row with Hamm.

08:14.040 --> 08:16.560
-Would you mind?
-I'm sorry, Hamm.

08:16.640 --> 08:19.040
It's no problem, I sometimes get confused

08:19.120 --> 08:22.760
with your British shirt sizes,
so perhaps Steven could give me a hand.

08:22.840 --> 08:25.720
-[jazzy music]
-[singers]  ♪ Hamm! ♪

08:25.800 --> 08:29.920
Every shirt, I mean every shirt,
looked sensational on him.

08:30.000 --> 08:31.840
And words cannot describe how great he is.

08:31.920 --> 08:34.159
Sounds like you have a bit of a crush
on Hamm, Toast.

08:34.240 --> 08:39.480
What, a crush on Jon Hamm?
You couldn't be more wide of the mark, Ed.

08:39.559 --> 08:44.120
Though I will admit,
the man certainly has charisma-a-a-a.

08:44.200 --> 08:48.200
-Care for a fancy, Toast?
-[camp] Ooh, don't mind if I do.

08:49.520 --> 08:51.440
[house creaks]

08:53.200 --> 08:54.640
These are delicious fancies, Ed.

08:54.720 --> 08:56.000
[loud crash]

09:00.560 --> 09:03.880
Any word on those replacement stairs?
Otherwise it's gonna be a pain in the arse

09:03.960 --> 09:06.240
having to use that ladder
each time we wanna go to bed.

09:06.320 --> 09:09.000
-It might be dry rot.
-[loud crash]

09:12.840 --> 09:14.080
Are you a fan of Jon Hamm, Ed?

09:14.160 --> 09:15.480
Oh, yes.

09:15.560 --> 09:19.240
I've got every series of  Mad Men  on DVD.
It's pretty much the best show on telly.

09:19.320 --> 09:21.640
Yeah, I'd heard it's great.
I'd love to see them.

09:21.720 --> 09:24.240
-Well...
-Now. I'd love to see it now.

09:24.320 --> 09:26.120
-Yeah, all right.
-If I could see them now.

09:26.200 --> 09:28.040
-I'll try and dig them out.
-Quick as you can.

09:28.600 --> 09:30.360
-[music on TV]
-[laughs]

09:30.440 --> 09:32.400
What's he doing? [laughs]

09:32.480 --> 09:34.200
He's insane!

09:35.440 --> 09:37.640
[laughs loudly]

09:37.720 --> 09:39.040
Shit.

09:40.800 --> 09:44.360
And his show is both terrifying
and very funny.

09:44.440 --> 09:47.440
And he is hilarious and quite mad in it.

09:47.520 --> 09:50.000
-[phone rings]
-It sounds like your phone, Toast.

09:50.080 --> 09:51.080
Ah.

09:52.600 --> 09:54.320
-Who's Blair?
-[phone continues ringing]

09:54.400 --> 09:55.760
It's your brother, you idiot.

09:55.840 --> 09:58.480
You should answer it, Toast.
It'll be about your father.

09:58.560 --> 10:00.360
-Who?
-Your father.

10:01.080 --> 10:02.080
Toast!

10:02.160 --> 10:04.520
-I'm giving you my position.
-What?

10:04.600 --> 10:08.480
I'm somewhere between
Sherborne and Crewkerne.

10:08.560 --> 10:10.760
I'll phone you with information
when I arrive.

10:11.400 --> 10:15.120
But make sure you're here by Friday,
Toast, and don't bloody forget!

10:15.200 --> 10:18.280
-What the hell are you talking about?
-Gone!

10:18.840 --> 10:19.840
He's hung up.

10:21.120 --> 10:23.880
Anyway, any word from Hamm?
Has he asked about me?

10:23.960 --> 10:25.760
Not that I recall.

10:25.840 --> 10:30.320
Ooh, he's just moved into a flat
in London. Meard Street, above the deli.

10:30.400 --> 10:33.760
-Isn't that opposite you?
-Opposite me and Ed, yes.

10:33.840 --> 10:36.480
I could show him some local haunts.
Have you got his number?

10:36.560 --> 10:38.040
Hamm is a major celebrity.

10:38.120 --> 10:40.640
I can't give out his number
to any Tom, Dick or Toast.

10:40.720 --> 10:43.360
-He might have it hacked.
-[intercom buzzes]

10:43.440 --> 10:45.960
-Yes, India, what is it?
-[India]  It's Peter Davison again.

10:46.040 --> 10:47.040
[sighs]

10:47.960 --> 10:50.240
Davison's cut his finger off
opening a letter?

10:51.000 --> 10:52.280
All his fingers or just one?

10:52.360 --> 10:54.440
Oh, hang on, I'll have to come out.

10:54.520 --> 10:55.720
I'll be back in a minute.

10:59.760 --> 11:01.320
-[singers]  ♪ Hamm! ♪
-[jazzy music]

11:03.120 --> 11:04.200
Here we are.

11:05.080 --> 11:08.520
Tony Hatch, Judith Hann,
Jimmy Hill, Jon Hamm.

11:08.600 --> 11:10.200
There's the boy.

11:10.280 --> 11:11.840
[singers]  ♪ Hamm! ♪

11:14.240 --> 11:17.000
-Hello?
-Hi, Hamm, it's Steven Toast here.

11:17.080 --> 11:18.520
Oh. Yes, hello.

11:18.600 --> 11:21.800
Oh, God. Um... how's it going your end?

11:21.880 --> 11:23.640
Everything's great.

11:23.720 --> 11:28.560
Listen I... I was just... wondering
if you fancied going for a drink sometime.

11:29.960 --> 11:31.680
-When were you thinking?
-Uh, tomorrow.

11:32.760 --> 11:34.120
I could do tomorrow afternoon.

11:34.880 --> 11:36.440
But I can't stay late.

11:36.520 --> 11:38.240
I'm shooting tomorrow in Dor-set.

11:38.320 --> 11:40.960
No, no, that's fine. That is amazing.

11:41.040 --> 11:43.840
Listen, we'll meet upstairs
at The Colonial,

11:43.920 --> 11:47.960
we'll sink a few,
and then maybe go for an Italian for two.

11:51.120 --> 11:53.600
Look, or whatever.
Let's meet at one o'clock.

11:53.680 --> 11:55.720
-Yes.
-Perfection.

11:55.800 --> 11:57.880
[Jane] Staunch the flow, India!

11:59.120 --> 12:00.320
Bloody hell!

12:02.040 --> 12:04.920
Davison's only gone
and lopped his middle finger off.

12:05.000 --> 12:06.680
Tried not to make a fuss in front of him,

12:06.760 --> 12:10.680
but when the bandages are off,
it will look quite odd.

12:11.440 --> 12:13.920
Ha! Never a dull moment!

12:17.320 --> 12:18.320
Toast.

12:19.560 --> 12:20.560
Are you all right?

12:20.640 --> 12:22.800
[blissful music]

12:26.960 --> 12:31.720
Oh, hello again. Have you thought any more
about that personal tuition idea?

12:31.800 --> 12:34.040
-Wha..?
-You could come to my flat if you want.

12:34.120 --> 12:38.400
I've got a sauna and Jacuzzi.
Maybe we could relax afterwards.

12:38.480 --> 12:40.120
[snorts]

12:51.480 --> 12:52.800
[sighs]

12:57.800 --> 12:59.280
[romantic music]

13:04.320 --> 13:06.200
[gasps]

13:06.280 --> 13:07.600
[groans]

13:12.040 --> 13:17.120
♪ I've got myself in a terrible jam ♪

13:17.200 --> 13:21.840
♪ I hit my head and now I fancy a man ♪

13:22.400 --> 13:26.800
♪ I should feel up,
I've never felt so down ♪

13:26.880 --> 13:32.440
♪ And they say
I'm the worst actor in town ♪

13:32.520 --> 13:34.000
♪ You're the worst ♪

13:34.960 --> 13:36.680
♪ Yes, you are ♪

13:37.560 --> 13:39.800
[sinister laugh]

13:42.480 --> 13:44.640
♪ You ♪

13:44.720 --> 13:47.240
♪ Are the worst actor ♪

13:47.320 --> 13:50.120
♪ In the wo-orld ♪

13:50.200 --> 13:54.200
♪ Who-o-o-o ♪

13:56.800 --> 13:59.400
[marching tune]

14:07.640 --> 14:08.960
[turns music off]

14:09.400 --> 14:11.440
Is this something to do
with you meeting Hamm later?

14:11.520 --> 14:12.520
No.

14:12.600 --> 14:14.600
You're not making a mix tape
for him, are you?

14:14.680 --> 14:15.680
No.

14:15.760 --> 14:18.680
He's probably not interested in those
old marching tunes you're so fond of.

14:18.760 --> 14:20.200
And recording them on cassette?

14:20.280 --> 14:23.960
It's very old fashioned. It's all
SoundCloud and Spotify these days.

14:26.680 --> 14:27.760
Oh, dear.

14:28.360 --> 14:32.040
I don't know what I'm doing.
It's been a while since I've been...

14:32.560 --> 14:35.080
-In love?
-Why the hell would you say that?

14:35.160 --> 14:37.320
Well, you're not eating,
you're not sleeping,

14:37.400 --> 14:39.160
you're keeping a diary.

14:39.240 --> 14:40.520
You've got all the symptoms.

14:40.600 --> 14:41.880
You don't understand.

14:41.960 --> 14:44.880
He's got this charisma.
It's like black magic.

14:44.960 --> 14:46.560
Jane says he draws everyone in.

14:46.640 --> 14:48.480
Why don't I make you
a cup of hot chocolate,

14:48.560 --> 14:50.080
and we can talk about this like adults?

14:50.800 --> 14:53.200
I don't think this obsession
with Hamm is healthy.

14:53.280 --> 14:56.000
You don't know him
and you don't understand me.

14:56.080 --> 14:57.800
And I hate living here!

14:58.840 --> 15:00.240
And I'm going to my room.

15:04.480 --> 15:05.720
And I've forgotten my ladder.

15:09.320 --> 15:12.360
Did you know that every phone line
in Hollywood is connected to an asshole?

15:13.840 --> 15:16.720
Hundreds of guys
waiting to fuck you over.

15:16.800 --> 15:20.160
But it's good to be back
filming in the UK.

15:20.240 --> 15:23.520
Dor-set is lovely this time of the year.

15:25.320 --> 15:26.440
What...

15:26.520 --> 15:28.000
Wait, are you crying?

15:28.080 --> 15:31.760
God, no. It's just that you...
you speak so eloquently, Hamm.

15:31.840 --> 15:33.920
-Oh.
-You really do.

15:34.000 --> 15:36.280
It's like hearing one's own name
mentioned on the wireless.

15:38.000 --> 15:40.000
You don't fancy a stroll
in the park, do you?

15:40.080 --> 15:43.120
-I mean, only if you're free, that is.
-I'm free until five.

15:43.200 --> 15:44.200
Only till five?

15:44.280 --> 15:48.040
What have you got on?
A photo shoot? A cocktail soirée?

15:48.120 --> 15:50.240
[laughs] A dental appointment.

15:50.320 --> 15:54.760
Well, your teeth look so perfect
when you play the Mad Man!

15:58.720 --> 15:59.720
Let's go.

15:59.800 --> 16:01.040
[singers]  ♪ Hamm! ♪

16:01.560 --> 16:04.280
[upbeat music]

16:05.120 --> 16:06.040
[singers]  ♪ Hamm! ♪

16:10.720 --> 16:14.040
-[singers]  ♪ Hamm! ♪
-That was the best fun I've ever had.

16:14.720 --> 16:15.960
I've got an idea.

16:16.640 --> 16:18.760
You're filming in Dorset, right?

16:18.840 --> 16:22.360
I need to be in Somerset in the morning.
We could travel down together.

16:22.440 --> 16:24.560
You could meet my father.

16:24.640 --> 16:26.000
Have to look sharp, he's dying.

16:26.520 --> 16:30.040
I dunno, I... I don't like being around
dying people. I feel like it's bad luck.

16:30.120 --> 16:31.440
Oh, come on!

16:31.520 --> 16:34.840
I could show you my father's castle.
It's the tallest in the world!

16:34.920 --> 16:36.200
Well, I've got your number.

16:37.360 --> 16:40.640
-Uh, listen, this was--
-The best time you've ever had.

16:41.680 --> 16:43.320
-No.
-OK.

16:43.400 --> 16:45.920
So... I'm going to go.

16:46.520 --> 16:47.520
Cool.

16:48.720 --> 16:50.160
Yeah, maybe see you tomorrow.

16:54.080 --> 16:55.320
Oh, my God.

16:55.400 --> 16:57.880
-Steven, hi!
-God, not you again.

16:57.960 --> 17:00.120
-How are you?
-What do you want?

17:00.200 --> 17:01.920
Myself, and a lot of other girls,

17:02.000 --> 17:05.400
who are actresses and models,
are going yachting over the weekend.

17:05.480 --> 17:09.839
We would love for you to join us, so you
could tutor us in acting and modeling.

17:09.920 --> 17:13.720
Me and the girls really enjoy
topless sunbathing on the deck,

17:13.800 --> 17:17.200
but if you're bothered by that,
we can wear our bikini tops.

17:17.280 --> 17:19.800
I haven't got an auntie's whiff
about modeling!

17:19.880 --> 17:23.119
Is this some kind of ploy
to get me on your sex boat?

17:23.200 --> 17:26.880
And if it is,
then you're barking up the wrong acorn.

17:26.960 --> 17:27.960
[Pooky] Oh.

17:31.680 --> 17:33.040
What the hell is wrong with me?

17:34.160 --> 17:36.200
The man's like crack!

17:36.280 --> 17:38.600
He's like cra-a-ack! [gibbers]

17:43.480 --> 17:45.320
[spy music]

18:06.480 --> 18:07.680
[music stops]

18:09.800 --> 18:11.080
Toast, what are you doing here?

18:11.160 --> 18:16.520
Hamm, it's you. Your window was open.
I couldn't resist climbing in.

18:17.400 --> 18:21.480
Yes, well, I spend a lot of time
hiding in my bed to avoid the paparazzi.

18:21.560 --> 18:25.760
It has a special Hamm-shaped indentation,
so that it appears to be flat.

18:26.920 --> 18:27.920
What's with the mask?

18:29.560 --> 18:32.040
It's Lovejoy, the antiques guy.

18:33.760 --> 18:35.760
Do you wear that so you're not recognized?

18:35.840 --> 18:39.560
No. I just went to the shop
They had a bunch of them.

18:39.640 --> 18:41.640
Mr. Bean, the Queen,
Camilla, Prince Charles.

18:41.720 --> 18:44.080
-I just liked the Lovejoy.
-[laughs]

18:45.200 --> 18:47.360
You certainly are a mad man!

18:48.000 --> 18:49.560
[phone rings]

18:51.560 --> 18:52.760
-Yep?
-[Blair]  I'm here.

18:52.840 --> 18:56.680
I've not entered the premises yet,
but on first look,

18:56.760 --> 18:58.880
it seems to be pretty vulture free.

18:58.960 --> 19:00.760
Blair, what the shit
are you talking about?

19:00.840 --> 19:01.840
Don't jigger me about.

19:01.920 --> 19:04.680
You need to get here
before the relatives descend.

19:04.760 --> 19:06.320
There could be dozens of them.

19:06.400 --> 19:08.600
I can't afford
to find myself outnumbered, Toast.

19:09.480 --> 19:11.400
[Toast] Outnumbered, you say?

19:11.480 --> 19:15.360
Don't worry about that, Blair.
I can bring someone with me.

19:15.440 --> 19:21.640
He's fit and has bags of charisma-a-a-a.

19:21.720 --> 19:22.840
What?

19:22.920 --> 19:24.680
-Hamm?
-Yes.

19:24.760 --> 19:26.960
It's about time you met my father.

19:29.280 --> 19:30.720
That is one tall castle.

19:31.280 --> 19:32.880
[Toast] Tallest in the world.

19:37.800 --> 19:41.520
I, Gonville Toast,

19:41.600 --> 19:45.720
I wish for my paintings, my gold,

19:45.800 --> 19:49.480
and my dog to be buried with me.

19:49.560 --> 19:50.560
[dog whines]

19:50.640 --> 19:54.160
Paintings, gold, dog to be buried
with you upon your death.

19:54.240 --> 19:58.840
[Toast] Father, I'm here!
Your son has arrived!

19:58.920 --> 20:02.680
-Who said that?
-That's your other son, Father. The actor.

20:02.760 --> 20:05.760
The actor? I thought he was dead!

20:05.840 --> 20:08.000
No, Father,
that's just what you tell everybody

20:08.080 --> 20:10.360
because you hate him. Is that you, Toast?

20:10.440 --> 20:13.400
We're at the top, in Father's bedroom.
Come quickly!

20:13.480 --> 20:18.840
And my firearms collection
shall be left to...

20:18.920 --> 20:21.120
Annie Lennox.

20:22.040 --> 20:23.280
And finally...

20:24.120 --> 20:25.320
Hurry up, Toast!

20:25.400 --> 20:26.960
And finally...

20:27.040 --> 20:28.920
[coughs]

20:29.480 --> 20:34.200
...I leave my entire estate, my fortune,

20:34.280 --> 20:39.600
and my freehold properties,
both here and in London to...

20:40.360 --> 20:43.240
[angelic music]

20:44.840 --> 20:46.800
Jon Hamm.

20:46.880 --> 20:47.880
Jon Hamm.

20:48.680 --> 20:49.920
-What?
-[groans]

20:50.000 --> 20:51.440
[Toast] Nooo!

20:51.960 --> 20:54.480
No, Father. Wait!

20:54.560 --> 20:56.320
Father! Wake up, Father!

20:56.400 --> 20:59.000
Wake up! Oh, dear God!

20:59.080 --> 21:01.320
I believe your father has passed.

21:02.760 --> 21:05.720
[Blair] This is your doing, Toast.
You bloody fool!

21:05.800 --> 21:07.720
Why did you bring Jon Hamm in here?

21:07.800 --> 21:11.120
Everyone knows about his charm
and charisma!

21:11.200 --> 21:12.920
I'm going to kill you!

21:13.000 --> 21:15.280
[Toast] Whoa!

21:15.360 --> 21:18.480
-Toast!
-Whoa!

21:18.560 --> 21:19.680
-Ooh!
-Oh, dear.

21:20.000 --> 21:22.200
[wails]

21:22.280 --> 21:25.000
-Oooh.
-Whoa!

21:25.080 --> 21:27.080
Whoa! Who-oa!

21:27.160 --> 21:28.600
-Christ!
-[yells]

21:32.720 --> 21:33.720
[groans]

21:35.680 --> 21:38.280
Can someone get me a cab?
I don't like being around dead people.

21:41.920 --> 21:43.920
Ah, good morning, Toast. You're back.

21:44.000 --> 21:45.920
-Feeling any better?
-Much better, thanks.

21:46.000 --> 21:49.520
Possibly due to my brother Blair
throwing me down 200 steps.

21:49.600 --> 21:51.640
Seems to have reset my head.

21:51.720 --> 21:54.480
Just to warn you, I had to give the ladder
back to Maureen Lipman.

21:54.560 --> 21:56.160
-Really?
-So we're going to have to use

21:56.240 --> 21:58.000
this length of rope
to get to our bedrooms.

21:58.080 --> 22:00.240
-But isn't that Hywel Bennett's?
-Yes.

22:00.320 --> 22:01.760
And we have to give that back soon

22:01.840 --> 22:04.000
so he can tie his horsebox
to his Lamborghini.

22:04.080 --> 22:06.800
Wait a moment, Toast,
shouldn't you be with your father?

22:06.880 --> 22:08.640
Too late, Ed. He's dead.

22:08.720 --> 22:11.280
Oh, I'm so sorry. How's Blair taking it?

22:11.360 --> 22:13.920
Not well.
I've never seen a man so furious.

22:14.000 --> 22:16.160
Possibly due to the fact
him not being left the castle

22:16.240 --> 22:18.280
or in fact anything in the will.

22:18.360 --> 22:20.480
-And who did he leave it to?
-Jon Hamm!

22:20.560 --> 22:23.040
Really? Well, he does have charm

22:23.120 --> 22:26.520
and the most enormous amount of charisma.
So yes, I'm not at all surprised.

22:26.600 --> 22:27.720
-Hm.
-Anyway,

22:27.800 --> 22:29.520
glad to have you back to normal.

22:31.520 --> 22:34.040
Ooh, she's just my type.

22:34.120 --> 22:36.880
Who's that slice of good beauty?

22:36.960 --> 22:39.040
Oh, it's a complete unknown
called Pooky Hook.

22:39.120 --> 22:41.640
-[gasps]
-No stage or screen experience,

22:41.720 --> 22:44.040
-and has landed a lead role in  Star Wars.
-[inhales deeply]

22:44.120 --> 22:46.320
Here she mentions
that she's a great fan of yours.

22:46.400 --> 22:49.240
Does she now? [laughs suggestively]

22:49.320 --> 22:51.600
Maybe you could give her
some acting lessons.

22:51.680 --> 22:54.720
Maybe I could. Maybe I could.

22:55.480 --> 22:57.960
-She's a cracker, don't you think?
-[laughs]

22:58.040 --> 23:02.920
-Probably too young for you!
-[both laugh]

23:10.320 --> 23:13.000
♪ So take my hand ♪

23:13.080 --> 23:15.440
♪ We'll disappear to a pub ♪

23:15.520 --> 23:18.200
♪ That's not too far from here ♪

23:18.280 --> 23:22.040
♪ Though I don't know you
and you don't know me ♪

23:22.120 --> 23:26.320
♪ I just had to talk to you, you see ♪

23:26.400 --> 23:27.920
♪ So take my hand ♪
